    <item xmlns:default="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/">
      <title>X recovers from ‘brief’ global outage
</title>
      <link>https://www.dawn.com/news/1973799/x-recovers-from-brief-global-outage</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;PARIS: Service was fully restored to the social network X on Monday afternoon following a widespread technical &lt;a href="https://www.dawn.com/news/1973704/x-briefly-hit-by-international-outages-monitors"&gt;disruption&lt;/a&gt; that left users across multiple continents staring at blank feeds and unable to view new posts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The outage, which str­u­ck the platform owned by Elon Musk, rendered the site largely inaccessible for approximately two hours before timelines began populating and functionality returned to normal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The platform appeared to be operating as usual by 3:30pm GMT. The restoration came shortly after Down Detector, a website that tracks online service interruptions, recorded a sharp spike in user reports regarding the site’s performance earlier in the afternoon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Downdector indicated that in Pakistan, the number of users reporting issues peaked at 6:54pm with a total of 275 complaints, subsequently decreasing to 8 by 7:54pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During the disruption, internet connectivity monitor Netblocks posted on the open-source social network Mastodon that X appeared to be suffering “international outages”.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;figure class='media  w-full  w-full  media--left  media--embed  media--uneven media--tweet' data-original-src='https://x.com/netblocks/status/2023392622249668648'&gt;
        &lt;div class='media__item  media__item--twitter  '&gt;&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/netblocks/status/2023392622249668648"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Netblocks, which tracks technical issues on major platforms as well as government-imposed internet shutoffs, clarified that Monday’s breakdown was “not related to country-level internet disruptions or filtering”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access issues were verified globally, with journalists in countries including France and Thailand reporting an inability to access the platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Representatives for X did not immediately resp­ond to requests for comment regarding the cause of the outage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Published in Dawn, February 17th, 2026&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
      <content:encoded xmlns="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><![CDATA[<p>PARIS: Service was fully restored to the social network X on Monday afternoon following a widespread technical <a href="https://www.dawn.com/news/1973704/x-briefly-hit-by-international-outages-monitors">disruption</a> that left users across multiple continents staring at blank feeds and unable to view new posts.</p>
<p>The outage, which str­u­ck the platform owned by Elon Musk, rendered the site largely inaccessible for approximately two hours before timelines began populating and functionality returned to normal.</p>
<p>The platform appeared to be operating as usual by 3:30pm GMT. The restoration came shortly after Down Detector, a website that tracks online service interruptions, recorded a sharp spike in user reports regarding the site’s performance earlier in the afternoon.</p>
<p>Downdector indicated that in Pakistan, the number of users reporting issues peaked at 6:54pm with a total of 275 complaints, subsequently decreasing to 8 by 7:54pm.</p>
<p>During the disruption, internet connectivity monitor Netblocks posted on the open-source social network Mastodon that X appeared to be suffering “international outages”.</p>
    <figure class='media  w-full  w-full  media--left  media--embed  media--uneven media--tweet' data-original-src='https://x.com/netblocks/status/2023392622249668648'>
        <div class='media__item  media__item--twitter  '><span>
    <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en">
        <a href="https://twitter.com/netblocks/status/2023392622249668648"></a>
    </blockquote>
</span></div>
        
    </figure>
<p>Netblocks, which tracks technical issues on major platforms as well as government-imposed internet shutoffs, clarified that Monday’s breakdown was “not related to country-level internet disruptions or filtering”.</p>
<p>Access issues were verified globally, with journalists in countries including France and Thailand reporting an inability to access the platform.</p>
<p>Representatives for X did not immediately resp­ond to requests for comment regarding the cause of the outage.</p>
<p><em>Published in Dawn, February 17th, 2026</em></p>
